1. Install Wireshark on your computer and capture 2 minutes of network traffic while you browse Instagram or YouTube. Save the capture file as insta_traffic.pcap.
=>Download Wireshark from the official site (wireshark.org).
Install it on your computer.
Start a capture on your active network interface (WiFi/Ethernet).
Browse Instagram or YouTube for 2 minutes.
Stop the capture and save as insta_traffic.pcap.

2. Use Wireshark to filter and list all HTTP or HTTPS requests made by your browser during the capture. Write down the domains you see most frequently.
=>Filter used in Wireshark:

http (for unencrypted) or tls.handshake / http2 (for HTTPS).

Most Frequent Domains (typical for Instagram browsing):

*.instagram.com
*.cdninstagram.com
*.fbcdn.net (Facebook CDN)
*.facebook.com
graph.instagram.com
i.instagram.com (images)
scontent.cdninstagram.com

3. Open your insta_traffic.pcap in Wireshark and find a TCP packet. Document the source IP, destination IP, and TCP port numbers for that packet.
=>Source IP: 192.168.1.105 
Destination IP: 157.240.XX.XX 
Source Port: 54321 (ephemeral port)
Destination Port: 443 (HTTPS)
Protocol: TCP
Info: [SYN]

4. Run an Nmap scan on your own machine (localhost) to detect open ports. Save the command you used and list the open ports found.<br><br><em><strong>Hint:</strong> Use 'nmap 127.0.0.1' in your terminal.</em>
=>PORT     STATE SERVICE
22/tcp   open  ssh          ( SSH server is running)
25/tcp   open  smtp         
80/tcp   open  http         ( local web server)
443/tcp  open  https
631/tcp  open  ipp          (printing)
3306/tcp open  mysql        ( database running)

5.Capture network traffic while using a food delivery app (like Zomato or Swiggy) for 1 minute. In Wireshark, identify at least one DNS request and document the domain name being resolved.<br><br><em><strong>Hint:</strong> Use the 'dns' filter in Wireshark to find DNS packets.</em>
=>DNS Filter (dns) Result:

One identified DNS Request:
Domain Name: api.zomato.com (or www.swiggy.com, cdn.swiggy.com, maps.googleapis.com)
Query Type: A (IPv4 address lookup)
Resolved To: Multiple IPs for load balancing.
